<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1450,2027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,260,1935,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Note:</emphasis>
The species name refers to the broad lobes on the sides of the aedeagal shaft. Like 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Duzee" authorityName="Van Duzee" box="[1140,1391,1935,1958]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Erasmoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubricata">
<emphasis box="[1140,1270,1935,1958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">E. rubricata</emphasis>
Van Duzee
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dmitriev &amp; Dietrich" authorityName="Dmitriev &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,528,1970,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Erasmoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="margaritae">
<emphasis box="[151,300,1970,1993]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">E. margaritae</emphasis>
Dmitriev &amp; Dietrich
</taxonomicName>
, this species has a broad and depressed aedeagal shaft. It differs in longer distal processes of the aedeagus and smaller size.
</paragraph>
